    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A colorless, flammable, quickly evaporating gas, vinyl chloride is a monomer principally used, in its refrigerated liquid form, to make polyvinyl chloride (PVC).  </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
